\newlabel{fig:timeline}{{16}{29}{Full cosmic timeline from DSC lattice dynamics ($128^3$). (a)~Planck SMICA target. (b)~DSC reconstructed CMB. (c)~Big Bang initial state ($t = 0$). (d)~CMB epoch ($t \sim 380$k~yr). (e)~Late universe with cosmic web ($t \sim 13.8$~Gyr). (f)~Galaxy clusters (high-density regions). (g)~Dark matter filaments (intermediate density). (h)~V-shape phase transition: field variance drops during adiabatic cooling (Phase~I) and rises during gravitational structure formation (Phase~II). The $1/\ln ^2(t)$ cooling naturally smooths primordial chaos without an inflaton field}{figure.16}{}}
